@page "/WorkOut";

<MudCard>

    <MudCardHeader>

        <CardHeaderContent>
            <MudText Typo="Typo.h6"><b>Skill Work</b> (10 mins)</MudText>
        </CardHeaderContent>

    </MudCardHeader>

    <MudCardContent>

        <MudCard Outlined="true">
            <MudCardContent>
                <MudText><b>HandStand Progression</b> (5-10 minutes)</MudText>
                <MudText Typo="Typo.body2" onclick="location.href='https://www.reddit.com/r/bodyweightfitness/wiki/exercises/handstand/'">
                    You're not supposed to hold a HS for 5-10 minutes nonstop. Hold it for 20-60secs (not to failure for safety reasons!)
                    and then come down, rest and go back up again whenever you are ready. Emphasize quality of form over quantity of time.
                </MudText>
            </MudCardContent>
            <MudCardActions>
                <MudButton Variant="Variant.Text" Color="Color.Primary" Href="https://youtu.be/qLLJWmHlYZQ?t=58">
                    Video
                </MudButton>
            </MudCardActions>
        </MudCard>
        @*This will go through the hand stand progression Perhaps these should be their own cards?*@

        <MudCard Outlined="true">
            <MudCardContent>
                <MudText><b>L-Sit Progression</b> (2-3 Minutes)</MudText>
                <MudText Typo="Typo.body2" onclick="location.href='https://www.reddit.com/r/bodyweightfitness/wiki/exercises/l-sit/'">
                    Arms pointing slightly out from "straight up". Protract hard then slide your arms up the wall.
                </MudText>
            </MudCardContent>
            <MudCardActions>
                <MudButton Variant="Variant.Text" Color="Color.Primary" Href="https://youtu.be/gF-8XCHcbxc">
                    Video
                </MudButton>
            </MudCardActions>
        </MudCard>
    </MudCardContent>

    <MudCard>

        <MudCardHeader>

            <CardHeaderContent>
                <MudText Typo="Typo.h6"><b>Mobility Work</b></MudText>
            </CardHeaderContent>

        </MudCardHeader>
        @*        Needs to be some kind of functionality here that'll let the user pick their mobility work group*@
        <MudCardContent>
            <MudCard Outlined="true">
                <MudCardContent>
                    <MudText><b>Front Splits</b></MudText>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.body2" onclick="location.href='https://redefiningstrength.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/deadbugmodified.jpg'">
                        The dead bug exercise is performed on the ground, so you need roughly the same amount of space as a yoga mat. And, you probably want to use a yoga mat or another type of exercise mat for comfort.
                    </MudText>
                </MudCardContent>
                <MudCardActions>
                    <MudButton Variant="Variant.Text" Color="Color.Primary" Href="https://youtu.be/x9Uz9zmW3Nk?t=50">Video</MudButton>
                </MudCardActions>
            </MudCard>

        </MudCardContent>

    </MudCard>

    <MudCardActions>
        <MudButton Variant="Variant.Text" Color="Color.Primary" Href="WorkOut">Finish Workout</MudButton>
    </MudCardActions>

</MudCard>

